{"title_page": "Andrei Gusev", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=March 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name         = Andrei Gusev\n| image        = Andrei Gusev.jpg\n| imagesize    = \n| alt          =\n| caption      = Andrei Gusev in 2000\n| pseudonym    =\n| birth_name    = Andrei Evgenievich Gusev\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1952|10|27}}\n| birth_place   = [[Moscow, Russia|Moscow]], [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic|Russian SFSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   =\n| occupation   = writer, novelist, journalist, inventor\n| nationality  = Russian\n| ethnicity    = \n| citizenship  = Soviet (1952\u201391)<br/>Russian (1992\u2013present)\n| education    =\n| alma_mater   = [[National Research Nuclear University MEPhI|Moscow Engineering Physics Institute]]\n| period       = 1990\u2013present\n| genre        = fiction, [[fantasy]], [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]], [[erotica]]\n| subject      =\n| movement     = [[Postmodern literature|Postmodernism]]\n| notableworks = [[With Chronos' Permit]]<br/> On the Edge of Magellanic Clouds<br/> [[The World According to Novikoff]] \n| spouse       =\n| partner      =\n | children     =\n| relatives    =\n| party        = \n| otherparty   = \n| influences   = \n| influenced   = \n| awards       =\n| signature    =\n| website      = {{URL|gusev.webs.com}}\n| portaldisp   =\n|module         =  \n}}'''Andrei Evgenievich Gusev''' ({{lang-ru|link=no|\u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u0415\u0432\u0433\u0435\u043d\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0413\u0443\u0441\u0435\u0432}}, born 27 October 1952) is a Russian writer and journalist. He is the author of 10 inventions, 23 published scientific works.<ref name=\"Bio\">[http://gusev.webs.com/Bio-en.htm Biography of Andrei E. Gusev]</ref> One of his co-authors is a winner of the Nobel Prize, a legend of the Soviet physics, the academician [[Alexander Prokhorov]].<ref>[http://www.findpatent.ru/byauthors/1190233/ \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \u0430\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u0413\u0423\u0421\u0415\u0412 \u0410\u041d\u0414\u0420\u0415\u0419 \u0415\u0412\u0413\u0415\u041d\u042c\u0415\u0412\u0418\u0427]</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nAndrei Gusev was born in former [[Soviet Union]], in Moscow. His parents were engineers. His father Evgeny Gusev was born in Chernihiv Oblast of Ukraine; his mother Rosalind Maltseva was born in Moscow.<ref name=\"Rodovid\">[https://en.rodovid.org/wk/Person:1166195  Andrei E. Gusev in Rodovid]</ref>\n\nAndrei Gusev graduated the [[National Research Nuclear University MEPhI|Moscow Engineering Physics Institute]] in 1975. The next eleven years he worked as a scientific employee (a medical physicist) in public health services. Also in these years he received a medical education.<ref name=\"VIP\">[http://viperson.ru/people/gusev-andrey-evgenievich Andrei E. Gusev on VIPERSON.ru]</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n[[File:Andrei E. Gusev in 2009.jpg|thumb|right|220px| Andrei Gusev in Moscow, 2009]] \nIn 1990 Andrei Gusev became a correspondent of the daily \"[[Moskovskij Komsomolets]]\". Later he worked as the special correspondent of the All-Russia \"[[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]]\" and dep. editor-in-chief of the youth newspaper \"Stupeni\".<ref>\u041d\u0410 \u041f\u041e\u0420\u041e\u0413\u0415  XXI \u0412\u0415\u041a\u0410, \u0412\u0441\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0435\u0436\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043a, \u041c., \"\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0430\u0441\", 2002 (\u0441.92)</ref><ref>\u0412\u0441\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0435\u0436\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043a \u041d\u0410 \u041f\u041e\u0420\u041e\u0413\u0415  XXI \u0412\u0415\u041a\u0410, \u041c., \"\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0430\u0441\", 2006 (\u0441.85)</ref>\n\nSince 1993 Andrei Gusev serves as editor-in-chief of [[New Medical Gazette|\"The New Medical Gazette\"]] (published in Russian).<ref>[http://nmgazette.narod.ru/ \"The New Medical Gazette\" (\u00ab\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430\u00bb)] (in Russian)</ref>\n\nAndrei Gusev is the author of several hundreds articles in \"[[Moskovskij Komsomolets]]\", \"[[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]]\", \"[[Sovetskaya Rossiya]]\", \"[[Vechernyaya Moskva]]\", \"[[The Moscow News]]\", \"Stupeni\", [[New Medical Gazette|\"The New Medical Gazette\"]], magazines \"Auto M\", [[:ru:\u0421\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 (\u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b)|\"Stolitza\"]], \"Yatt\" etc.<ref name=\"Bio\"/>\n\nWithin work in \"Stupeni\" the first books of the writer were published: a collection \"Ticket to America\" (1992) and \"Presentation\" (1993). Then he published \"Mister Novelist\" (1994), \"[[With Chronos' Permit]]\" (1995), \"The Russian Story\" (1996)  and also the story collection \"On the Edge of Magellanic Clouds\" (1998).<ref name=\"VIP\"/> He published his novels \"The Painter & Eros\" and \"Role Plays\" in 2003 and  \"[[The World According to Novikoff]]\" in 2007.\nIn his prose in the 2010s Andrei Gusev developed the themes of [[BDSM]] subculture in Russia. Themes include [[Dominatrix|female domination]], [[Bondage (BDSM)|bondage]], [[spanking|erotic spanking]] and [[BDSM]] fiction.<ref>[http://proza.ru/2016/03/10/50  \u00ab\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u043e\u0431\u043e\u0436\u0430\u0435\u0442 role plays\u00bb (\u201cThe Russian Writer Loves Role Plays\u201d)] \u2013  a story by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>[http://lady.webnice.ru/forum/viewtopic.php?t=21732 \u041f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u00ab\u0416\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0432 BDSM\u00bb (\u201cThe Writers\u2019s Wife Likes BDSM\u201d)] in Lady's Club {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>[http://lady.webnice.ru/forum/viewtopic.php?t=22336 \u041f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u00ab\u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0443\u043c\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u043c\u0431\u0430\u0441\u0435\u00bb (\u201cConsummation in Mombasa\u201d)] in Lady\u2019s Club {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>[https://gusev.webs.com/Malindi.htm  \u201cOur Wild Sex in Malindi\u201d] \u2013  a story by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\nAndrei Gusev served as a prototype<ref>\u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432 [http://old.cultradio.ru/doc.html?id=520936 \"\u0414\u0438\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433 \u0443\u043c\u0430 \u0438 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430\"], \"\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430\", 19 \u043e\u043a\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044f 2013 \u0433.</ref> for one of the main characters \u2013 Andrei Lebedev, a journalist of the newspaper ''Moskovskij Bogomolets'', which is very similar to the famous ''[[Moskovskij Komsomolets]]''  \u2013 in the thriller novel \"[[Journalists (novel)|Journalists]]\" by [[Sergei Aman]].  In the novel by the same author \"Everything Will Be Okay, We're All Going to Die!\"<ref>''\u0410\u043c\u0430\u043d \u0421.'' \u00ab\u0412\u0441\u0451 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442 \u0445\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0448\u043e, \u043c\u044b \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0440\u0451\u043c!\u00bb \u042d\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0433\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u044d\u043f\u043e\u0441. \u2014 \u041c.: \u0418\u0414 \u00ab\u0424\u043b\u044e\u0438\u0434 \u0424\u0440\u0438\u0424\u043b\u0430\u0439\u00bb, 2018. \u2014 {{ISBN|978-5-906827-70-8}}</ref> Gusev was described under his own name, as a journalist Andrei Gusev.\n\n==Personal life==\nAndrei Gusev lives in Moscow. He was married twice and divorced twice. The first wife  \u2013  Nina Guseva (n\u00e9e Odnoletko), worked as a nurse; the second wife  \u2013  Ivetta Sarkisyan, philologist by education. He has two daughters.<ref name=\"Rodovid\"/>  \nHis hobby is beekeeping.\n\n==Selected bibliography<ref>[http://bvi.rusf.ru/fwho/0421.htm/ \u0424\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430: \u043a\u0442\u043e \u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043a\u0442\u043e]</ref><ref>[http://www-lat.rusf.ru/fc/d0210.htm \u041f\u0430\u043c\u044f\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0434\u0430\u0442\u044b \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0444\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, \u043e\u043a\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044c 2002 (27 \u043e\u043a\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044f)]</ref><ref>[http://nmgazette.narod.ru/100years.htm  \u00ab\u0421\u0442\u043e \u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0440\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u00bb]</ref>==\n\n*Andrei Gusev  \"PRESENTATION\", motley stories, Moscow, 1993.\n*Andrew E. Gusev \"MISTER NOVELIST\", stories and short stories, Moscow, 1994.\n*Andrei E. Gusev  \"[[With Chronos' Permit|WITH CHRONOS\u2019 PERMIT]]\", stories, film-novel, Moscow, 1995.\n*Andrei E. Gusev  \"THE RUSSIAN STORY\", novel, Moscow, 1996.\n*\"ON THE EDGE OF MAGELLANIC CLOUDS\", collection of the stories and short stories, Moscow, 1998, publishing house \"Probel\", {{ISBN|5-89346-012-X}}.\n*Andrei E. Gusev  \"THE PAINTER & EROS\", novel, Moscow, 2003, publishing house \"West-Consulting\", {{ISBN|5-85511-011-7}}.  \n*Andrei E. Gusev \"ROLE PLAYS\", stories, Moscow, 2003, publishing house \"West-Consulting\".\n*Andrei E. Gusev  \"[[The World According to Novikoff]]\", novel, Moscow, 2007, publishing house \"West-Consulting\", {{ISBN|978-5-903321-02-5}}.\n\n==Online text==\n*[[:ru:s: \u0421\u0442\u043e \u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0440\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f|\u0421\u0442\u043e \u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0440\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f]] \u2013  a story by Andrei Gusev in Wikisource {{in lang|ru}}\n*[[:ru:s: \u041f\u0443\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0446\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043b\u044e\u0431\u0432\u0438|\u041f\u0443\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0446\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043b\u044e\u0431\u0432\u0438]] \u2013   a short story by Andrei Gusev in Wikisource {{in lang|ru}}\n*[[:ru:s: \u00ab\u041e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u044c\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0435\u043c \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u0441\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0430!\u00bb|\"\u041e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u044c\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0435\u043c \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u0441\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0430!\"]] \u2013   a short story by Andrei Gusev in Wikisource {{in lang|ru}}\n*[http://proza.ru/2016/03/10/50  The Russian Writer Loves Role Plays] \u2013  a story by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}\n*[https://www.proza.ru/2018/02/07/58  Love Story in the Style of Femdom] \u2013  a novel by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}\n*[https://gusev.webs.com/Malindi.htm  Our Wild Sex in Malindi]  \u2013  a novel by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Russian-language writers]]\n* [[List of Russian-language novelists]]\n* [[List of thriller writers]] \n* [[List of BDSM authors]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n {{Commons category}}\n* [http://andrei-gusev.narod.ru/ Official website of Andrei Gusev] {{in lang|ru}}\n* [http://www.gusev.webs.com  Editor-in-Chief of \"New Medical Gazette\" Andrei E. Gusev (from Moscow)]\n*[http://www.facebook.com/writer.Gusev Official page  of Andrei Gusev in Facebook]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gusev, Andrei}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Writers from Moscow]]\n[[Category:Russian male novelists]]\n[[Category:Russian male short story writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Russian writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian short story writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Russian short story writers]]\n[[Category:Russian fantasy writers]]\n[[Category:Thriller writers]]\n[[Category:BDSM writers]]\n[[Category:Russian journalists]]\n[[Category:Russian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Russian newspaper editors]]\n[[Category:Moscow Engineering Physics Institute alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n\n[[ru:\u0413\u0443\u0441\u0435\u0432, \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u0415\u0432\u0433\u0435\u043d\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447|\u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u0415\u0432\u0433\u0435\u043d\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0413\u0443\u0441\u0435\u0432]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=March 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name         = Andrei Gusev\n| image        = Andrei Gusev.jpg\n| imagesize    = \n| alt          =\n| caption      = Andrei Gusev in 2000\n| pseudonym    =\n| birth_name    = Andrei Evgenievich Gusev\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1952|10|27}}\n| birth_place   = [[Moscow, Russia|Moscow]], [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic|Russian SFSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n| death_date    =\n| death_place   =\n| occupation   = writer, novelist, journalist, inventor\n| nationality  = Russian\n| ethnicity    = \n| citizenship  = Soviet (1952\u201391)<br/>Russian (1992\u2013present)\n| education    =\n| alma_mater   = [[National Research Nuclear University MEPhI|Moscow Engineering Physics Institute]]\n| period       = 1990\u2013present\n| genre        = fiction, [[fantasy]], [[Thriller(genre)|thriller]], [[erotica]]\n| subject      =\n| movement     = [[Postmodern literature|Postmodernism]]\n| notableworks = [[With Chronos' Permit]]<br/> On the Edge of Magellanic Clouds<br/> [[The World According to Novikoff]] \n| spouse       =\n| partner      =\n | children     =\n| relatives    =\n| party        = \n| otherparty   = \n| influences   = \n| influenced   = \n| awards       =\n| signature    =\n| website      = {{URL|gusev.webs.com}}\n| portaldisp   =\n|module         =  \n}}'''Andrei Evgenievich Gusev''' ({{lang-ru|link=no|\u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u0415\u0432\u0433\u0435\u043d\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0413\u0443\u0441\u0435\u0432}}, born 27 October 1952) is a Russian writer and journalist. He is the author of 10 inventions, 23 published scientific works.<ref name=\"Bio\">[http://gusev.webs.com/Bio-en.htm Biography of Andrei E. Gusev]</ref> One of his co-authors is a winner of the Nobel Prize, a legend of the Soviet physics, the academician [[Alexander Prokhorov]].<ref>[http://www.findpatent.ru/byauthors/1190233/ \u041f\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \u0430\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u0413\u0423\u0421\u0415\u0412 \u0410\u041d\u0414\u0420\u0415\u0419 \u0415\u0412\u0413\u0415\u041d\u042c\u0415\u0412\u0418\u0427]</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nAndrei Gusev was born in former [[Soviet Union]], in Moscow. His parents were engineers. His father Evgeny Gusev was born in Chernihiv Oblast of Ukraine; his mother Rosalind Maltseva was born in Moscow.<ref name=\"Rodovid\">[https://en.rodovid.org/wk/Person:1166195  Andrei E. Gusev in Rodovid]</ref>\n\nAndrei Gusev graduated the [[National Research Nuclear University MEPhI|Moscow Engineering Physics Institute]] in 1975. The next eleven years he worked as a scientific employee (a medical physicist) in public health services. Also in these years he received a medical education.<ref name=\"VIP\">[http://viperson.ru/people/gusev-andrey-evgenievich Andrei E. Gusev on VIPERSON.ru]</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n[[File:Andrei E. Gusev in 2009.jpg|thumb|right|220px| Andrei Gusev in Moscow, 2009]] \nIn 1990 Andrei Gusev became a correspondent of the daily \"[[Moskovskij Komsomolets]]\". Later he worked as the special correspondent of the All-Russia \"[[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]]\" and dep. editor-in-chief of the youth newspaper \"Stupeni\".<ref>\u041d\u0410 \u041f\u041e\u0420\u041e\u0413\u0415  XXI \u0412\u0415\u041a\u0410, \u0412\u0441\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0435\u0436\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043a, \u041c., \"\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0430\u0441\", 2002 (\u0441.92)</ref><ref>\u0412\u0441\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0435\u0436\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043a \u041d\u0410 \u041f\u041e\u0420\u041e\u0413\u0415  XXI \u0412\u0415\u041a\u0410, \u041c., \"\u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u041f\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0430\u0441\", 2006 (\u0441.85)</ref>\n\nSince 1993 Andrei Gusev serves as editor-in-chief of [[New Medical Gazette|\"The New Medical Gazette\"]] (published in Russian).<ref>[http://nmgazette.narod.ru/ \"The New Medical Gazette\" (\u00ab\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u044f \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0433\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430\u00bb)] (in Russian)</ref>\n\nAndrei Gusev is the author of several hundreds articles in \"[[Moskovskij Komsomolets]]\", \"[[Rossiyskaya Gazeta]]\", \"[[Sovetskaya Rossiya]]\", \"[[Vechernyaya Moskva]]\", \"[[The Moscow News]]\", \"Stupeni\", [[New Medical Gazette|\"The New Medical Gazette\"]], magazines \"Auto M\", [[:ru:\u0421\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 (\u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b)|\"Stolitza\"]], \"Yatt\" etc.<ref name=\"Bio\"/>\n\nWithin work in \"Stupeni\" the first books of the writer were published: a collection \"Ticket to America\" (1992) and \"Presentation\" (1993). Then he published \"Mister Novelist\" (1994), \"[[With Chronos' Permit]]\" (1995), \"The Russian Story\" (1996)  and also the story collection \"On the Edge of Magellanic Clouds\" (1998).<ref name=\"VIP\"/> He published his novels \"The Painter & Eros\" and \"Role Plays\" in 2003 and  \"[[The World According to Novikoff]]\" in 2007.\nIn his prose in the 2010s Andrei Gusev developed the themes of [[BDSM]] subculture in Russia. Themes include [[Dominatrix|female domination]], [[Bondage (BDSM)|bondage]], [[spanking|erotic spanking]] and [[BDSM]] fiction.<ref>[http://proza.ru/2016/03/10/50  \u00ab\u0420\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c \u043e\u0431\u043e\u0436\u0430\u0435\u0442 role plays\u00bb (\u201cThe Russian Writer Loves Role Plays\u201d)] \u2013  a story by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>[http://lady.webnice.ru/forum/viewtopic.php?t=21732 \u041f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u00ab\u0416\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0432 BDSM\u00bb (\u201cThe Writers\u2019s Wife Likes BDSM\u201d)] in Lady's Club {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>[http://lady.webnice.ru/forum/viewtopic.php?t=22336 \u041f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u00ab\u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0443\u043c\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u043c\u0431\u0430\u0441\u0435\u00bb (\u201cConsummation in Mombasa\u201d)] in Lady\u2019s Club {{in lang|ru}}</ref><ref>[https://gusev.webs.com/Malindi.htm  \u201cOur Wild Sex in Malindi\u201d] \u2013  a story by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}</ref>\n\nAndrei Gusev served as a prototype<ref>\u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0438\u0439 \u041c\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432 [http://old.cultradio.ru/doc.html?id=520936 \"\u0414\u0438\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0433 \u0443\u043c\u0430 \u0438 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0430\"], \"\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u041a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430\", 19 \u043e\u043a\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044f 2013 \u0433.</ref> for one of the main characters \u2013 Andrei Lebedev, a journalist of the newspaper ''Moskovskij Bogomolets'', which is very similar to the famous ''[[Moskovskij Komsomolets]]''  \u2013 in the thriller novel \"[[Journalists (novel)|Journalists]]\" by [[Sergei Aman]].  In the novel by the same author \"Everything Will Be Okay, We're All Going to Die!\"<ref>''\u0410\u043c\u0430\u043d \u0421.'' \u00ab\u0412\u0441\u0451 \u0431\u0443\u0434\u0435\u0442 \u0445\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0448\u043e, \u043c\u044b \u0432\u0441\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0440\u0451\u043c!\u00bb \u042d\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e-\u0433\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u044d\u043f\u043e\u0441. \u2014 \u041c.: \u0418\u0414 \u00ab\u0424\u043b\u044e\u0438\u0434 \u0424\u0440\u0438\u0424\u043b\u0430\u0439\u00bb, 2018. \u2014 {{ISBN|978-5-906827-70-8}}</ref> Gusev was described under his own name, as a journalist Andrei Gusev.\n\n==Personal life==\nAndrei Gusev lives in Moscow. He was married twice and divorced twice. The first wife  \u2013  Nina Guseva (n\u00e9e Odnoletko), worked as a nurse; the second wife  \u2013  Ivetta Sarkisyan, philologist by education. He has two daughters.<ref name=\"Rodovid\"/>  \nHis hobby is beekeeping.\n\n==Selected bibliography<ref>[http://bvi.rusf.ru/fwho/0421.htm/ \u0424\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430: \u043a\u0442\u043e \u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043a\u0442\u043e]</ref><ref>[http://www-lat.rusf.ru/fc/d0210.htm \u041f\u0430\u043c\u044f\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0434\u0430\u0442\u044b \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0444\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, \u043e\u043a\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044c 2002 (27 \u043e\u043a\u0442\u044f\u0431\u0440\u044f)]</ref><ref>[http://nmgazette.narod.ru/100years.htm  \u00ab\u0421\u0442\u043e \u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0440\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u00bb]</ref>==\n\n*Andrei Gusev  \"PRESENTATION\", motley stories, Moscow, 1993.\n*Andrew E. Gusev \"MISTER NOVELIST\", stories and short stories, Moscow, 1994.\n*Andrei E. Gusev  \"[[With Chronos' Permit|WITH CHRONOS\u2019 PERMIT]]\", stories, film-novel, Moscow, 1995.\n*Andrei E. Gusev  \"THE RUSSIAN STORY\", novel, Moscow, 1996.\n*\"ON THE EDGE OF MAGELLANIC CLOUDS\", collection of the stories and short stories, Moscow, 1998, publishing house \"Probel\", {{ISBN|5-89346-012-X}}.\n*Andrei E. Gusev  \"THE PAINTER & EROS\", novel, Moscow, 2003, publishing house \"West-Consulting\", {{ISBN|5-85511-011-7}}.  \n*Andrei E. Gusev \"ROLE PLAYS\", stories, Moscow, 2003, publishing house \"West-Consulting\".\n*Andrei E. Gusev  \"[[The World According to Novikoff]]\", novel, Moscow, 2007, publishing house \"West-Consulting\", {{ISBN|978-5-903321-02-5}}.\n\n==Online text==\n*[[:ru:s: \u0421\u0442\u043e \u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0440\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f|\u0421\u0442\u043e \u043b\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u043e \u0434\u043d\u044f \u0440\u043e\u0436\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f]] \u2013  a story by Andrei Gusev in Wikisource {{in lang|ru}}\n*[[:ru:s: \u041f\u0443\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0446\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043b\u044e\u0431\u0432\u0438|\u041f\u0443\u0434\u0435\u043b\u044c \u0446\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u043b\u044e\u0431\u0432\u0438]] \u2013   a short story by Andrei Gusev in Wikisource {{in lang|ru}}\n*[[:ru:s: \u00ab\u041e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u044c\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0435\u043c \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u0441\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0430!\u00bb|\"\u041e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u044c\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0435\u043c \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u0441\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0430!\"]] \u2013   a short story by Andrei Gusev in Wikisource {{in lang|ru}}\n*[http://proza.ru/2016/03/10/50  The Russian Writer Loves Role Plays] \u2013  a story by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}\n*[https://www.proza.ru/2018/02/07/58  Love Story in the Style of Femdom] \u2013  a novel by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}\n*[https://gusev.webs.com/Malindi.htm  Our Wild Sex in Malindi]  \u2013  a novel by Andrei Gusev {{in lang|ru}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Russian-language writers]]\n* [[List of Russian-language novelists]]\n* [[List of thriller writers]] \n* [[List of BDSM authors]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links==\n {{Commons category}}\n* [http://andrei-gusev.narod.ru/ Official website of Andrei Gusev] {{in lang|ru}}\n* [http://www.gusev.webs.com  Editor-in-Chief of \"New Medical Gazette\" Andrei E. Gusev (from Moscow)]\n*[http://www.facebook.com/writer.Gusev Official page  of Andrei Gusev in Facebook]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gusev, Andrei}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Writers from Moscow]]\n[[Category:Russian male novelists]]\n[[Category:Russian male short story writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Russian writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian short story writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Russian short story writers]]\n[[Category:Russian fantasy writers]]\n[[Category:Thriller writers]]\n[[Category:BDSM writers]]\n[[Category:Russian journalists]]\n[[Category:Russian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Russian newspaper editors]]\n[[Category:Moscow Engineering Physics Institute alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Russian male writers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male writers]]\n\n[[ru:\u0413\u0443\u0441\u0435\u0432, \u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u0415\u0432\u0433\u0435\u043d\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447|\u0410\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0435\u0439 \u0415\u0432\u0433\u0435\u043d\u044c\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0413\u0443\u0441\u0435\u0432]]\n", "name_user": "Genericusername57", "label": "safe", "comment": "space", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrei_Gusev"}
